title: Goblet, ca. 1810–25
provenance: M.H. Impey, 172 Walton Street, London, SW3, (8-8-69) purchased by WPW.
description: Inverted pear-shaped bowl with flat bottom, short stem with ring knop. Plain circular foot. Engraved band with sketchy scalloped edges contains 4 sprigs inscribed in semicircular areas. Between them and abstract, dotted flowers.

tombstone.epitaph:
Goblet, ca. 1810–25.
ca. 1810–25. glass. Bequest of Walter Phelps Warren. 1986-61-208.
